As of midnight yesterday, South Korea had 516 new cases of coronavirus infection, 142 more cases than at 4 p.m. yesterday, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 5328, and the death toll to 32, the Central Epidemic Prevention Department of South Korea reported on March 4, the Cure increased to 41 cases.

So far, in addition to confirmed cases, 131379 people have been tested for the virus in South Korea, 10,340 have been added in 24 hours, with 102965 testing negative and 28,414 pending results.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Source: Korea Central Epidemic Prevention Countermeasures Department

Of the 5,328 confirmed cases as of midnight, 4,006 were in Taegu and 774 were in North Gyeongsang Province, accounting for 75.2% and 14.5% , respectively. On average, 164.4 and 29.1 cases per 100,000 people were confirmed in both places, with the remaining areas accounting for more than one to two cases and 10.3 cases per 100,000 people throughout the Republic of Korea.

Outside Taegu and Gyeongbuk, the country has 101 confirmed cases in Gyeonggi Province, 99 in Seoul, 93 in Busan, 82 in South Chungcheong Province and 65 in South Gyeongsang Province.

As of midnight on March 3, a total of 2,698 cases, accounting for 56.1% , had been confirmed in Xintiandi Church, the majority of which were from Taegu (2,383 cases) and Qingbei district (229 cases) .

It is noteworthy that more than 40 per cent (41.4 per cent) of all confirmed cases so far have been in the 20-40 age group, with women in their 20s making up a larger proportion. "Central Daily" on the 3rd pointed out that this is the new world church, a higher proportion of young female believers.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Sex and age distribution of 5328 confirmed cases were 62.5% females and 37.5% males. Source: Korea Central Epidemic Prevention Countermeasures Department

As of midnight, 192634(98.7 percent) of the 195162 followers of the new World Church had been contacted, the Central Disaster Safety Department said Wednesday. Of these, 13,241 had symptoms, of which 6,561 had been tested for the virus, and 62 per cent of Daegu believers were positive.

Seoul has charged new heaven and Earth Church President Lee Man-Hee and others with manslaughter, assault and violation of laws related to the prevention and management of infectious diseases on the 1st, while Lee Man-Hee knelt down on the 2nd to apologize, said he would cooperate with the government.

Seoul also said the city government had decided to revoke the Xintiandi legal person's license after deciding that the legal person had "harmed public welfare, " and would hold a hearing next week, the joongang Ilbo reported Wednesday. It is understood that the new World Church was incorporated in Seoul in November 2011.

Seoul Culture Minister Yoo yeon-sik pointed out that, "The new World Church has a responsibility to actively cooperate with the government and the epidemic prevention authorities, but it has repeatedly delayed, falsified and systematically avoided investigation when submitting lists of believers, and we understand that the church is still conducting missionary work and meetings in various underground venues. "

The number of countries and regions taking measures to control entry into South Korea has increased to 89 as of 3:00 pm Wednesday, according to the South Korean Foreign Ministry. Of these, 37 have imposed comprehensive or time-limited entry bans on South Korea, 22 have quarantined people from South Korea, and 30 have stepped up quarantine on people from South Korea.

According to Yonhap reported on the 4th, the South Korean government has prepared 11.7 trillion won (68.43 billion yuan) for the fight against the epidemic size of the supplementary budget, the supplementary budget will be submitted to parliament on the 5th. In addition to strengthening the epidemic prevention system, the government will also invest huge sums of money to stimulate the domestic market affected by the epidemic.

It was moon's fourth supplementary budget since his government was formed and the largest in seven years, surpassing the size of the budget enacted in 2015 when the Middle East Respiratory Syndrome epidemic spread.

Of the 11.7 trillion won supplementary budget, 8.5 trillion will be spent on various anti-epidemic projects, they include improving and upgrading the epidemic prevention system (2.3 trillion yuan) , supporting small and medium-sized enterprises and small businesses hit by the epidemic (2.4 trillion yuan) , invigorating the depressed local economy (800 billion yuan) , and stabilizing people's livelihood and employment (3 trillion yuan) , the remaining $3,200 BN will be used to close the tax gap. A special allocation of won600bn will be set aside for stabilising employment in Taegu and the Gyeongbuk region, where the outbreak is more severe.

Add in the 4 trillion won and 16 trillion won that are being implemented, and the South Korean government will spend more than 30 trillion won (175.47 billion yuan) fighting the epidemic.

South Korea's Vice Prime Minister and Planning Finance Minister, Hun Nam Ki, said the government considers supporting the economy to be a top priority and will actively push for the adoption of the supplementary budget and implement more than 75 percent of the budget within two months of its adoption.

Hong also said the day before, the government will issue 130 million masks to vulnerable groups free of charge, and will launch a number of initiatives to solve the epidemic difficult to buy masks.

He said he would strive to increase the country's daily production of masks to 14 million and would significantly increase the supply rate through the public distribution network, which is currently 50 percent, to 1,200 to 1,500 won (7 to 9 yuan) each.

Hong said that major pharmacies will start a monitoring system this week to prevent repeated purchases of masks, and that the government will provide production-increasing subsidies to mask manufacturers to ensure the supply of raw materials and other support; Imports of face masks from Brazil, South Africa and elsewhere will also be considered.

But he also said that at present, South Korea mask is still the best quality products, the products of the above countries are not up to the domestic KF80 level, so can not rely on imports.
